

AWS WAF is tightly integrated with Amazon CloudFront, the Application Load Balancer (ALB), Amazon API Gateway, and AWS AppSync 

services used to deliver content for websites and applications

WAF on CloudFront means all Edge Locations use your rules - close to end-users; so security doesn't come at the expense of performance

blocked requests are stopped before they reach web servers. 

If WAF is used on regional services (Application Load Balancer, API Gateway, AppSync), rules run in region and can protect internet-facing resources and internal resources..


WAF web ACL rules can be used to temporarily block users i.e. for excessive requests, based on regular rules or rate based rules

1. create a web ACL, 2. associate it with ALB 3. when a rule triggers, WAF applies the action to additional requests from the IP address until rate falls

cannot deny traffic using security groups

